<item>
            <title>[LU-10865] quota reintegration reported version and index count errors.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10865</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;One of Customers reported following errors when force quota reintegrations:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mar 29 01:30:20 xssds31 kernel: Lustre: 2007:0:(qsd_reint.c:246:qsd_reint_index()) lustre3-MDT0000: index version for fid &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x200000005:0x1016:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is 0, but index isn&apos;t empty (1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is easy to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&#160; &#160; 1.format Lustre and mount MDT/MGS, OST.

&#160; &#160; 2.lctl conf_param lustre.quota.mdt=ug

&#160; &#160; 3.lctl set_param osd-ldiskfs.*.quota_slave.force_reint=1

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;Then you will see some dmesg like above.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;Problem is osd-ldiskfs IAM will try to init one&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;zero entry initially, so for newly created slave index&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;file, there will be at least one entry for it, let&apos;s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;bump version properly to make reintegration check&#160;happy.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre master branch&lt;br/&gt;
osd-ldiskfs backend.</environment>
